00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:20,672
<i>Once inside the murky glen, Ichabod's</i>
<i>anxiety increased one-hundredfold.</i>

622
00:58:20,760 --> 00:58:24,230
<i>The forest seemed</i>
<i>to close in behind him.</i>

623
00:58:24,320 --> 00:58:27,790
<i>Every small detail</i>
<i>of Brom's awful story</i>

624
00:58:27,880 --> 00:58:30,838
<i>returned to haunt his recollection.</i>

625
00:59:32,520 --> 00:59:34,078
Headless Horseman.

626
01:00:13,720 --> 01:00:15,073
Beware!

627
01:02:56,680 --> 01:02:59,114
<i>Once you cross that bridge,</i>
<i>my friends,</i>

628
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:02,670
<i>the ghost is through,</i>
<i>his power ends.</i>

629
01:04:05,680 --> 01:04:09,070
<i>Next morning,</i>
<i>Ichabod's hat was found.</i>

630
01:04:09,600 --> 01:04:13,036
<i>And close beside it,</i>
<i>a shattered pumpkin.</i>

631
01:04:13,720 --> 01:04:17,076
<i>But there was no trace</i>
<i>of the schoolmaster.</i>

632
01:04:21,160 --> 01:04:25,870
<i>Shortly thereafter, Brom Bones</i>
<i>led the fair Katrina to the altar.</i>

633
01:04:27,320 --> 01:04:30,437
<i>Rumours persisted</i>
<i>that Ichabod was still alive,</i>

634
01:04:30,520 --> 01:04:33,557
<i>married to a wealthy widow</i>
<i>in a distant county.</i>

635
01:04:34,040 --> 01:04:38,318
<i>But the good Dutch settlers</i>
<i>refused to believe such nonsense.</i>

636
01:04:38,400 --> 01:04:41,836
<i>They knew the schoolmaster</i>
<i>had been spirited away</i>

637
01:04:41,920 --> 01:04:43,831
<i>by the Headless Horseman.</i>

638
01:04:47,200 --> 01:04:50,033
<i>With a hip-hip and a clippity-clop</i>

639
01:04:50,120 --> 01:04:52,793
<i>He's out looking for a head to swap</i>

640
01:04:52,880 --> 01:04:55,838
<i>But don't try to figure out a plan</i>

641
01:04:55,920 --> 01:05:02,917
<i>You can't reason with a headless man</i>

642
01:05:05,160 --> 01:05:06,991
<i>Man, I'm getting out of here!</i>

